SIMPLE: edification
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Edification
<hw>Ed`i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aedificatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧dification</ets>. See
<er>Edify</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of edifying, or the
state of being edified; a building up, especially in a moral or
spiritual sense; moral, intellectual, or spiritual improvement;
instruction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The assured <qex>edification</qex> of his church.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Out of these magazines I shall supply the town with what may tend
to their <qex>edification</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A building or edifice.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bullokar.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edificatory</ent>⟦br⟧
